    <p>Welcome to the 2013 listing of Northern California’s top car shows, auto shows and automotive events. Major car show and Auto show organizers have been preparing for this year’s shows since last year and this year is shaping up to be one of the best years for automotive events.</p>
<h2>Car Show Organizers</h2>
<p>Don’t forget to send us this year’s information for your car show! Click here to <a href="http://www.norcalcars.com/carshows/addacarshow.aspx">Register a Car Show</a> so we can help you promote your show.</p>
<i>Click on the links in the "Information" column to see Pictures and details of each show.</i>

    &nbsp;&nbsp;
    <p>Major Classic car show organizers like Good Guys, Pacific Coast Dream Machines Show, Kool April Nites and Concours are once again starring in this year’s calendar. International auto shows are once again scheduled for LA and San Jose, the Silicon Valley International Auto Show  and the Los Angeles Auto Show are providing a look at some of the concept cars from Ford, GM, and Toyota as well as the future in electric vehicles.</p> 
<p>We can also look forward to major auctions like Russo and Steele letting us dream of being among the bidders for some of the hottest cars to grace a show room floor. Filling in the gaps from the major shows are smaller, community, high school and city chamber based car show that give us events to check out  all over the state.</p>
